Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules Review Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules Review
Hello ladies,
Today, I shall be reviewing for you another product by Elemis! It is called Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules. Capsules? No, these are not capsules for consumption, they are for your face. How you might ask? Well read on to find out!

Product Description:
Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules contain pure Moringa Oil with its unique anti-ageing properties to dramatically renew skin elasticity and skin youthfulness. Anti-Oxidants physically repair the visible signs of ageing and counteract the damaging effects of pollution by weeping clean your network of skin cells, ridding it of harmful toxins. Use with Elemis Pro-Collagen Marine Cream for exceptional results.
Price:
£49.99
Ingredients:

Ingredients of Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules:
Pink/Day: Moringa Pterygosperma Oil, Fragrance (Parfum including a blend of Rose Absolute – Rosa
Centifolia), Citronellol, Geraniol, Linalool, Citral, Limonene.
Green/Night: Moringa Pterygosperma Oil, Fragrance (Parfum including a blend of Lavender Essential Oil –
Lavandula Angustifolia), Linalool, Limonene, Geraniol, Citral
Active Ingredients:

Moringa Oil.
Rose Absolute.
Lavender.

Directions For Use:
My Experience with Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules:
This Elemis Cellular Skin Bliss Capsules comes in a big frosted jar, the first impression that comes to my mind while looking at it, is that it is very clean and crisp! It has silver detailing and the lid is pure white. Inside the jar, there are two divisions made. One is for the pink capsules and the other is for the green capsules. The capsules are frosted pale pink and frosted pale green coloured. They seem very lush and it is definite that they belong to a luxurious high-end brand. As the instructions suggest, you have to twist these capsules open to release the product inside it. The product inside it, is basically an oil.

There are about 60 capsules that come in this jar and need to be used as directed on the back of the packaging. Now, let’s talk about the effects it has had on my skin. As you all know, my skin is really sensitive and so I was wary about using oil on my skin since I was sure that it would result in irritation. However, the lady at the salon, suggested I made use of this to get rid of my scars. I have used an oil by Clarins before as well and that too resulted in me breaking out, the complications of sensitive skin *sigh*. But I just went with the flow and finally purchased it. Now, the texture of the oils are not too heavy! They are lightweight and easily get absorbed into the skin, which was a relief because the oil from Clarins, just sat on my face and made me look really stupid. I applied both the capsules as instructed.

Pink Capsule:  It has a lovely fragrance, smells very floral and is calming to the senses. It has resulted in my pores being tightened and my skin feels extremely soft to touch. Also because you are meant to use this in the morning, because of its lightweight constancy, it will not result in any discomfort and application of makeup will also be smooth and you don’t have to worry about your makeup melting off with this oil.

Green Capsule:  This smells like lavender and since lavender is meant to relax the skin and flaring caused on it, I considered it to be promising and it surely lived up to my expectations. My skin felt really relaxed upon application, it also reduced any redness on my face, leaving me with a clearer complexion. Moreover, it has helped reduced my blemish marks marginally! Which is a great bonus!
In my opinion, I would only suggest using such oils during the winter. Otherwise, if you are living in hot climates, it might cause breakouts, because you might be at risk of clogged pores due to the humidity and oils are not what you must be applying then. Like if I was in Mumbai, I would be staying far way from this sort of a product.

Overall, I am pretty pleased with this product, I enjoy how I have not broken out *touchwood* and neither have I faced any irritation, instead it has soothed any irritation. However, I will suggest you not to wear this oil in areas of active breakouts.
Pros of Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules:

Both the capsules have helped recover my blemishes and open pores.
Have relatively softer and suppler skin to touch.
They both have lovely fragrance to it.
Makeup does not melt off, if you have applied this.
The lavender helps soothe irritation.
Great for the winters.

Cons of Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules:

Cannot or rather should not be used in hot climates.
Should not be used in instances of active breakouts.

Would I Repurchase Elemis Cellular Recovery Skin Bliss Capsules?
Next winters, I shall be purchasing it for sure.

Sephora haul Sephora started shipping to the UK a while ago, but whilst browsing I got a little frustrated that many brands were actually not able to be shipped over here. I decided to use Borderlinx (which I've used in the past) so I could ship my Sephora order to an address in the US, and Borderlinx then ship it to the UK. This option was more expensive than using Sephora's delivery service (it came to around 70 shipping and tax for $200 worth of Sephora goodies, Sephora would have charged around 35) but it did mean I could buy brands Sephora won't ship to us and I also made two separate $100 orders to maximise the free samples which bumped up delivery costs too.I made this order about a week before we had an offer accepted on a house so I'm currently feeling a bit guilty about spending so much! Since we've bought a house we probably won't be going to New York in December as we'd planned so this is a good substitute for a trolley-dash in Sephora (until next year anyway!). Read on to see what I bought:Josie Maran Argan Skincare Ritual ($24) - This value set is a great way to try out sample sizes of the products.Lavanila The Healthy Deodorant($8) - I'm curious to see if this is as effective as traditional deodorant.Fresh Sugar Lip Treatment - Passion ($22.50) - I already have the 'Tulip' shade and love it, this is a gorgeous rich red.Kat Von D Tattoo Liner ($18) - I just had to add this to my basket after Este's rave review!Anastasia Brow Wiz - Medium Brown ($21) - Continuing my love of brow products.Living Proof Perfect Hair Day ($26) - If it's good enough for Jennifer...Ole Henriksen The Clean Truth Brightening Cleansing Cloths ($15) - I hope these are worth the hype!Sephora Cream Lip Stain - Strawberry Kissed ($13) - I had to try this after seeing how fab it looks on Amelia.Shiseido Eyelash Curler Replacement Pads ($6) - These work in my Shu Uemura curler, which is great since Shu don't sell replacement pads!Sephora Single Ribbon Hair Ties ($1 each) - These hair-friendly ties are gentle and cause less breakages, the individuals are sold out but you can buy apack of 8 for $9.Sephora Summer Crushes ($45) - Although it seems that Summer is already over in the UK, there are plenty of interesting products I'll enjoy trying out in this set. See below to see the full contents:Jack Black Intense Therapy Lip Balm, Murad Essential-C Sun Balm, Supergoop! City Sunscreen Serum, DERMAdoctor Shrinking Beauty, Bumble and bumble Surf Spray, Vita Liberata pHenomenal 2-3 Week Tan Mousse in Medium plus mini tanning mitt,Caudalie Divine Oil,Shaveworks The Cool Fix, Living Proof Restore Mask Treatment, Lavanila Vanilla Coconut FragranceHere are the freebies I got:Ole Henriksen Wonders 7 Day Sample Set - free with $25 purchase use code WONDERSOle Henriksen Lemon Strip Flash Peel sample - free with $25 purchase use code PEELBliss Triple Oxygen+C Energising Cream samples - This moisturiser helps to revive dull skin.DERMAdoctor KP Duty Lotion samples - A moisturiser containing glycolic acid suitable for dry skinHourglass Mineral Veil 100 point perk(x2) - I couldn't justify a purchase of the full sized bottle without trying a sample first, and so far, so good!Jack Black Double Duty Face Moisturizer sample - I think this brand is more directed at men, I'll be interested to try out the texture and scent of the product.GlamGlow ThirstyMud Hydrating Treatment sample - Another much-hyped product I'll be interested to try!Thanks for reading! Have you bought anything from Sephora recently?P.S. Estee Lauder Private Collection, Perfume For The Bohemian Bourgeoisie Ahhh, oh how I love a gorgeous green perfume. Not the traditionally pretty ... but still somehow anti-establishment. I love it.
Talitha Getty  the ultimate Bohemian Bourgeoisie
Right now, Im getting my fix from Este Lauder Private Collection the original one released in 1973. I decided I had to have it after reading this awesome post ... Collection was Tammy Wynettes signature scent?). The best part of that post? Showing it to shocked sales associates at the Este Lauder counter who were clearly surprised to see anyone under sixty five asking for Private Collection. No really, I said. Its ... my beloved Ivoire de Balmain (vintage), that sexy skin vibe that the perfumes of the seventies do so well. Maybe Este Lauder Private Collection is closer to the original Vent Vert, but it is warmer and more casual than sharp edged VV. ... it might be a bit overdone. And overdone is not cool.
Veruschka  who else?
Despite the WASPy leanings of the Este Lauder line, and perhaps even Mme Lauder herself, this perfume is part of era that had the vibe of revolution. Women ... Private Collection belongs in the private collection of every woman who believes she deserves the very best life has to offer.Este Lauder, Founder
In her private office, Mrs. Lauder kept a collection of rare fragrance essences. She created a perfume from these ... scent were told it was from her private collection. Not to be denied, they began calling department stores to request Este Lauders Private Collection. In 1973, Mrs. Lauder bowed to popular demand and introduced her signature perfume to the world.
The notes in Private Collection, from the Este Lauder website:
Top Notes:
Honeysuckle, Jasmine, Citrus
Middle Notes:
Orange Flower, Ylang-Ylang, Coriander
Base Notes:
Sandalwood, Patchouli
What a lovely floral ... and strong. Notwithstanding Rihannas drugstore sugar drenched perfume offerings, I like to think she actually wears something as womanly as Este Lauder Private Collection. Because she would rock it.

Today's face So after posting a bit of a meh post yesterday I've picked myself up dusted myself down and I'm back, I got rid of my roots which always help the sun is shining and I've put on a face of makeup always makes you feel better.  I'm not going to moan about not having a Lint Easter egg although I would love one ha ha.So here is today's face:So what did I use to create this look:First of all I prepped the skin and used my:-Laura Mercier Foundation Primer: I find using a primer is essential now for makeup looks as if I don't use one your makeup tends to slip and slide off my face.  Recently I've been using my BD Trade Secrets Primer but I like to switch them around quite a bit.Nars: Foundation is for my base and the colour is Santa Fe my only gripe is the bottle doesn't have a pump, but I've purchased there newest foundation and this one has got the pump with it.Nars: Creamy Concealer in Light is one of my faves, it covers such a range of sins such as dark circles redness and it doesn't make your skin look patchy it's amazing.Chantecaiille: Loose powder in Subtle just to keep any pesky shine at bay.Chanel:  cream blush in Presage on the cheeks it looks quite scary in the pan but blended in looks quite natural I think .Anastasia: Contour kit I'm loving contouring still, and love being able to fake cheek bones which I haven't really got as I've got chubby cheeks.On the eyes:I've mixed a bit of Mac Patina and Cranberry over my lids and lined my upper lash line with Estee Lauder Double Wear eyeliner in Olive Lustre, I love this I think it's such a pretty shadeOn my lower lash line I've used cranberry to line and on the lashes it's my mini Benefit Rollerlash.Lip wise it's Nars  Audacious in Bridget.And last but not least a swipe  of  Hourglass lightening palette to fake my glow on my face.I quite liked today's look for a change:)You might think it's quite a lot and it is but I'm off visiting friends later so I'm hoping it will hold till thenHave a good night guysLaura

Au Fudge: Inside Jessica Biel’s New Mom-centric L.A. Restaurant 
For mamas that love to lunch, the options are two-fold: make reservations someplace lovely and deal with a squirming child for an hour or two or settle for a kid-friendly restaurant and deal with the sub-par food and lack of ambiance.
A few Hollywood mamas have answered the prayers of ladies who lunch (with children) across the city by opening up the doors of Au Fudge, an enchanting, but casual restaurant that allows mothers to dine out with their children and get the best of both worlds. Au Fudge has all the beautiful bells and whistles w'ere looking for in any restaurant: ambiance for days, a killer organic menu and bar that serves up elegant cocktails like the one below. In addition, the restaurant's menu is filled with ultra kid-friendly dishes (that are healthy too) and offers moms the option to send the kiddos into a beautiful play room where they can craft, read and play for hours under the supervision of their in-house au pairs!
We think this savvy team of founders is on to something - the hotspot has already gained popularity with famous moms from Rachel Zoe to Alessandra Ambrosio. Au Fudge's stellar team includes L.A. mamas Kimberly Muller, Jessica Biel, and Monica Saunders-Weinberg, as well as designer Estee Stanley (which helps explain the beautiful space!), Joey Gonzalez of Barry's Bootcamp and Jonathan Rollo of Greenleaf Gourmet Chopshop.
The space is also the first restaurant to receive the Environmental Media Association's "EMA Green Seal,” which speaks to just how thoughtfully the space was designed to keep green values throughout. The glassware is vintage and the kitchen runs at maximum energy efficiency - great green lessons to teach children at every turn.
We think the Au Fudge concept is genius - and here to stay! What do you think, readers? Kiddos or no, would you visit a restaurant where children can be whisked away to play, only after eating the best organic meals? We know it's very L.A., but we think this food concept is 100%!

New York: the haul Confession time. I went in to 5 different Sephora’s in 5 days in NY. Now, I don’t feel like that’s TOO excessive given the fact that they all seem to be slightly different, but some of your may disagree.Anyhow, I was determined to try and track down stuff that I couldn’t get in the UK rather than spend all my hard-earned cash on things that were *slightly* cheaper, but easily available at home.Annoyingly, there seemed to be some sort of Manhattan-wide Kat Von D shortage, as all of the products/shades I was after were out of stock in every single Sephora I went into. Disappointing. I guess I’ll have to make an online order for that instead; clearly everyone wanted the same nude shades as me.Anyhow, I did manage to spend quite a few $$$ while I was there, mixing it up with Sephora and the drugstores. Duane Reade is the drugstore of choice in New York – they seem to have one on every street. It’s a weird mix of beauty products and groceries, so you can stock up on peanut butter M&Ms while you peruse the tampons and Milani.If I’m honest, I found the drugstores a little overwhelming – there was so much choice, but they don’t seem to label what’s new, so it was quite hard to pick out bits and pieces without a good ol’ Google session beforehand.I’d seen the Maybelline Vivid Matte Liquids thanks to Jane from British Beauty Blogger, so grabbed one of those and also tracked down some Milani Lip Oils, which seem to be a similar thing to the GOSH ones I reviewed a few weeks ago.I seem to be allergic to EOS lip balms which sucks as they’re so nice, so instead I bought a mini hand cream from them to keep in my handbag. There was also the obligatory Wet n Wild Walking on Eggshells palette – the perfect neutral eye shadow trio.Although I’d heard a LOT about Bath & Body Works, I’d never actually been to one before, so made it my mission to get up to the one near the Flat Iron building the day I arrived. The number of scents they stock is just unreal – you need a good hour to browse and sniff your way through the shelves! I ended up with 5 mini pocket anti-bacs in different fruity/citrus scents, as well as two fragrances mists and a matching body cream. I’m kinda wishing I had bought myself a 3 wick candle or two now, but I was a bit worried about fitting it all in my suitcase, so resisted the urge.Sephora-wise, I knew I had to grab one of the cream lip stains, so I found Pink Souffle a pinky-nude that I know I’ll wear a lot. I also found the new Luster Matte Liquids which are of a similar pigment level, but with a glossier finish, so went a bit bolder on that one and tried out Orchid Luster. There was an entire counter dedicated to colour-correcting, so thought I'd give their redness corrector a try, as well as picking up the new Blotterazzi by Beauty Blender which seems like an interesting concept! After spending several visits tracking down the new Estee Edit range, I decided to give the Flash Photo Powder a try, as it promises to give an almost Instagram filter finish to your skin. Fingers crossed!I made a few skincare purchase too - a Sephora sachet mask, Josie Maran's argan trial kit, a mini Glam Glow cleanser (which will hopefully launch here later this year) and a Too Cool For School Egg Mousse Pack which I'd heard very good things about.As it was my birthday month, I got a little Sephora reward as part of their points card system, giving me a very cute Marc Jacobs beauty duo. I'd highly recommend getting one of their loyalty cards - not only do you get birthday gifts and points, but there are also special offers galore. Even if it's just for a single visit, you can still earn some decent points if you like a good haul!On our trip to Chelsea Market, Kelsey and I had a quick whizz around all of the craft stalls and I fell in love with the canvas makeup bags. The New York slogan definitely appealed and it's the perfect size to pop in my handbag with all my new makeup. I also found Limegreen, an artisan brand from Brooklyn who make natural skincare and body products. Their Lemongrass oil was too good to resist, so I had to bring a bottle home with me.At the time it felt like I didn't buy a huge amount, but looking back at it all definitely proves me wrong. Oops. I'll be doing some reviews on a few of these products over the new few weeks - let me know if there's anything you'd like to see more info on!Read all of my New York posts...
